25/10/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha met with Kosovo counterpart Bajram Kosumi in Tirana on Monday (24 October).
At a joint news conference afterwards, Berisha reiterated his stance that Kosovo must gain independence, while guaranteeing the rights of the Serb minority and other minorities.
He also stressed the importance of serious and continued dialogue between Pristina and Belgrade.
In turn, Kosumi said that Kosovo Albanian leaders view independence as the only viable solution to the province's problems.
(Albanian News - 25/10/05;
KosovaLive - 24/10/05)
